CAPE TOWN - MPs are calling for an investigation into allegations of bribery by State Security Minister, Bongani Bongo. He's been accused of trying to stop an investigation into Eskom by bribing key officials. LIVE STREAM: Brian Molefe to testify at state capture hearing All MPs condemned the minister's alleged actions with EFF calling on the Public Protector to investigate the allegations. Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises is continuing its inquiry into allegations of corruption at Eskom. eNCA